data.description: WATERFRONT HOME WITH GULF ACCESS! Impressive *FURNISHED* 3 Bedroom, 2 Bathroom home with attached oversized 2 Car Garage located in a quiet neighborhood in Port Charlotte. Close to all amenities. NO HOA. This light and bright home offers an open and split bedroom floor plan with Great Room, separate Dining Room, well appointed Kitchen, Inside Laundry. The Great Room features a double tray ceiling, crown molding, wood look tile floor and access to the Lanai. The Dining Room has natural light through a large window. The Kitchen features custom 42 inch cabinets, New stainless appliances, tile backsplash, granite counters, wood cabinets, good storage space, pantry closet, breakfast bar and dining area. The spacious Kitchen dining area has a wonderful view of the pool and waterfront thru Aquarium glass. The Inside Laundry has a washer, dryer, sink, granite countertops and cabinets. The spacious Master Bedroom suite has a double tray ceiling, TWO walk in closets and private bathroom with his and hers sinks, vanity area to apply your makeup, granite counters, soaking tub and walk in shower.  There are two good sized guest bedrooms, one with a walk in closet. The guest bathroom has a tub/shower combo and granite counters. Your living space extends via sliding glass doors to the screened Lanai and pool area with large covered area, plenty of deck for sunbathing, 23x12 inground heated saltwater pool and paver deck. A great spot to enjoy your morning coffee while taking in the view of the pool, waterfront and native Florida birds. Continue to the waterfront with 80 FOOT concrete seawall, 2 tiered wood dock with canopy covered 8000 lb boat lift, water, electric and a rack that will accommodate two kayaks. 25 minutes to open water (Charlotte Harbor) and only one bridge. Other features include: *NEW ROOF March 2023*, new A/C 2018, new pool pump 2018, new exterior paint, wood look tile floors throughout the living areas and bedrooms, rain gutters, 12x10 exterior storage shed with electricity, plantation shutters, crown molding, high ceilings, tray ceilings. Utilities are county water and sewer. Move in Ready!  *Motivated Sellers!* This home is perfect for a family or those expecting lots of winter visitors. Located minutes from shopping, dining, Charlotte Sports Park, waterfront parks, boat ramps, fishing piers, medical care, entertainment. This is Florida living at its finest!
